cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI 

This paper is about a new model for supervised learning to rank, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions that learning to rank methods can be applied to natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text classification and sentiment analysis, which fall under the sub-categories of cs.CL and cs.AI. Additionally, the paper mentions that the proposed method can be applied to image retrieval, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV.
